		<p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b4d0525d677b6f81c929583af8fb569b?s=48&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.createdinbirmingham.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FCiB%2Fimages%2Fcibavatar.png&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b4d0525d677b6f81c929583af8fb569b?s=96&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.createdinbirmingham.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FCiB%2Fimages%2Fcibavatar.png&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' itemprop="image" />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.fiercetv.co.uk' rel='external nofollow' class='url fn n' itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">helga</span></a></cite>		</p>
		<p class="comment-meta"> 
			<time class="comment-published" datetime="2009-04-03T21:21:18+00:00" title="Friday, April 3, 2009, 9:21 pm" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="http://www.createdinbirmingham.com/2009/04/03/birmingham-library/#comment-49403">April 3, 2009 at 9:21 pm</a></time>
					</p>
		<div class="comment-content">
			<p>Why didn&#8217;t BCC appoint a UK based architect?  Because it was an international competition, carried out under procurement regulations, and a Dutch company won.  </p>
<p>Dont&#8217; get me wrong, I think it would have been wonderful if an Birmingham based company had got it &#8211; but they didn&#8217;t.  But now this (Dutch)firm will open a base in Brum and employ local architects.  </p>
<p>And let&#8217;s not forget that our local architects, and any UK firms, are free to compete for the contract to design Dutch libraries &#8211; or any library or building in any EU country.  That&#8217;s how the EU works.</p>
<p>Norman Foster and partners is an architecture practice of international reknown &#8211; when he designed Hong Kong airport I don&#8217;t think we jumped up and down saying &#8220;It&#8217;s a shame they didn&#8217;t use local architects&#8221;.  When Frank Geary did the Guggenhiem in Bilbao everyone thought it was a coup for Bilbao.</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s instead take this as a rallying call for local architects to compete on the world stage &#8211; I can&#8217;t wait for the day that you report on this blog that some of our fantastic design talent, like Glenn Howells, has won the opportunity to design a major building in a city elsewhere in the world.</p>
